net.dv8tion.jda.client.managers

Class EmoteManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.client.managers.EmoteManager

  • public class EmoteManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Decoration for a EmoteManagerUpdatable instance.
    Simplifies managing flow for convenience.

    This decoration allows to modify a single field by automatically building an update RestAction

      • setName

        public AuditableRestAction<java.lang.Void> setName(java.lang.String name)
        Sets the name of the selected Emote.

        An emote name must be between 2-32 characters long!
        Emote names may only be populated with alphanumeric (with underscore and dash).

        Example: tatDab or fmgSUP

        Parameters:
        name - The new name for the selected Emote
        Returns:
        AuditableRestAction
        Update RestAction from #update()
        Throws:
        InsufficientPermissionException - If the currently logged in account does not have the Permission MANAGE_EMOTES
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the provided name is null or not between 2-32 characters long
        See Also:
        EmoteManagerUpdatable.getNameField(), EmoteManagerUpdatable.update()

      • setRoles

        public AuditableRestAction<java.lang.Void> setRoles(java.util.Set<Role> roles)
        Sets the restriction roles of the selected Emote.
        If these are empty the Emote will be available to everyone otherwise only available to the specified roles.

        An emote's restriction roles must not contain null!

        Parameters:
        roles - The new not-null set of Roles for the selected Emote to be restricted to
        Returns:
        AuditableRestAction
        Update RestAction from #update()
        Throws:
        InsufficientPermissionException - If the currently logged in account does not have the Permission MANAGE_EMOTES
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If any of the provided values is null
        See Also:
        EmoteManagerUpdatable.getRolesField(), EmoteManagerUpdatable.update()
